reviewText: This is an adorable DVD with both Bubble Guppies and Team Umizoomi.  I was a little bummed to see there was only three episodes on it but it is still DVD for kids who like those adorable Nickelodeon characters.  The DVD is just about an hour long in total and since its broken down into episodes its easy to watch just one or watch them all.  These are episodes that have been on tv so your child may have already seen them, but that doesn't bother my kids.Bubble Guppies - Happy Holidays, Mr. Grumpfish!Team Umizoomi - A Sledding DayTeam Umizoomi - City of Lost Penguins
Title: Bubble Guppies / Team Umizoomi: Into the Snow We Go!

reviewText: This DVD contains three Winter Holiday themed episodes from the Bubble Guppies and Team Umizoomi.  Amazon doesn't always do a good job on their DVD episode listings so here are the episodes that are included on this DVD:1. Bubble Guppies - Happy Holidays, Mr. Grumpfish! - Mr. Grumpfish doesn't like the holidays, or does he?2. Team Umizoomi - A Sledding Snow Day - UmiCar become UmiSled for sledding fun.3. Team Umizoomi - City of Lost Penguins - Baby penguins escape and the team must rescue them.
Title: Bubble Guppies / Team Umizoomi: Into the Snow We Go!

reviewText: Two year old Jonah loves the Bubble Guppies.  Couldn't take his eyes off them.  Mom loved them too because now he can watch them at home.
Title: Bubble Guppies / Team Umizoomi: Into the Snow We Go!

reviewerName: Randall F. Miller III "Randy Miller III"
reviewText: This half-hearted collection only includes three episodes from the popular Nick shows "Bubble Guppies" and "Team Umizoomi".  The first two ("Happy Holidays, Mr. Grumpfish" and "A Sledding Snow Day") fit the bill: these chilly adventures are lightly educational and entertaining at times.  "Team Umizoomi" is definitely the weaker show, but since that episode follows the winter theme it's at least tolerable.  Unfortunately, the third episode ("City of Lost Penguins") has very little to do with winter: a group of 50 penguins is scattered from the zoo and the team must rescue them using math, patterns, and all their typical tricks to outsmart The Trouble Makers.  So basically, there are three episodes (60 minutes total) and only about 40 minutes of snow.In my opinion, only the "Bubble Guppies" episode is worth watching more than once, and the $15 price tag for what amounts to 60 minutes of cartoons is pretty much a rip-off.  If that weren't enough, these episodes (like most Nick DVDs) are cropped to "full screen"...which is silly, because almost everyone has a widescreen TV, monitor or tablet by now (even Grandma!).  Only desperate relatives in need of a cheap stocking stuffer will settle for this collection; otherwise, leave it on the shelf.  There's no shortage of worthwhile holiday DVD/Blu-ray titles that give you much more bang for the buck.
summary: Partly cloudy with a 66% chance of snow
Title: Bubble Guppies / Team Umizoomi: Into the Snow We Go!

reviewText: It will be a miracle if this DVD makes it to Christmas! We have to watch it over and over, even the Umizoomis!
Title: Bubble Guppies / Team Umizoomi: Into the Snow We Go!
